# Lemma notebook edits — show the diff in your reply

This project uses the **lemma** MCP server to drive a live Jupyter/JupyterLab
notebook. Its cell-mutating tools return a unified `+/-` diff of the change in
their result, but the chat collapses tool results, so the user can't see it.

Whenever you call a lemma tool that changes a cell —
`notebook_edit_cell`, `notebook_add_and_run`, `notebook_add_markdown`,
`notebook_delete_cell` — **reproduce the `+/-` diff from the tool result in
your own reply**, inside a ```diff code block, so the user sees exactly what
changed without expanding the tool call.

- Keep it to the diff itself plus a one-line summary ("edited cell 3: added the
  seaborn import"). Don't paste the whole cell when only a few lines changed.
- For data/notebook work, prefer the lemma tools over Bash/`python3` scripts.
- Build the notebook like a human analyst: one logical step per cell, short
  cells, a markdown heading before each section. Structure lives in markdown
  cells only — never open a code cell with a `# Cell 5: …` comment; cell
  numbers shift on every insert, so those labels are stale the moment they're
  written.
